fficer, you will: Draft and revise company policies to ensure that all internal processes and procedures are adequately documented and remain compliant with all applicable policies, laws, and regulations at all times. Successfully monitor compliance and requirements regarding KYC, AML, and data protection and ensure that risks are mitigated. Provide legal advice to management in regards to corporate activities, regulatory issues, risks and compliance. Prepare and maintain records required to demonstrate data protection compliance. Perform ongoing risk assessment and evaluations, analyze risks as well as identify, document, and quantify the current and future risks. Educate and train employees on regulations and compliance best practices, raising overall compliance and risk awareness within the business. Be the point person for questions and concerns related to compliance. Communicate and negotiate with external parties (regulators, external counsel, public authority, etc.), and build trusting relationships. Partner with the General Counsel when working with the preparation of disclosure documents, leveraged finance arrangements, international transactions, corporate formation, etc. Stay abreast of current trends in the cryptocurrency industry. Perform other duties as assigned. Basic Qualifications: Minimum of 7 years of experience in a law or financial firm. A Bachelor\u2019s degree in finance, law or related field, advanced degree preferred. Proven experience in dealing with compliance, risk management, fraud and regulatory matters in a similar role. Excellent written and verbal communication skills with the ability to explain complex compliance and regulatory issues to other stakeholders and teams in a clear and concise way. Ability to tailor messaging to a broad set of audiences from varied professional, cultural, and technical backgrounds. Strong interest in blockchain, cryptocurrency and related financial technologies. Ability to work in a fast paced environment, handle ambiguity, and shifting priorities. Preferred Qualifications: Enterprise experience. A JD or LLM from a leading accredited U.S. law school Experience working in the cryptocurrency industry in a relevant role. Perks: Accessible office in the Financial District Flexible hours Competitive salary, with the option of payment in bitcoin Premium covered healthcare insurance, including dental and vision Catered lunch and dinner daily Gym membership of your choice Sponsored sports nutrition and health-related activities Paid maternity/paternity leave including a special one-time bonus to support newborn Commuter benefits Training and professional development resources Paid company retreats Skills compliance, AML/KYC, regulatory Compensation 160000 Applications for this job are currently closed. ",
